<subSubSection id="F7A718B050045134C4DD5B5E85B865FE" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D449D1DF28E80E834FB0F5BDB94DF40A" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C440429C6E2ACF2B2B56124657EA0DF7" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">A subsp. typo habitu suberecta et foliis triangularibus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="484EE3DF1FEF677DDE376E7373C8DE25" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="5D00D604A64A594478D69F2F922BC068" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis subsp. var. var. erectus" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="arvensis" subSpecies="var." variety="erectus">Convolvulus arvensis var. erectus</taxonomicName>
Ledeb., Fl. Altaic. [Ledebour] 1: 224. 1829. (
<bibRefCitation id="F356CA63C115EBE81721761AAD689496" author="Ledebour, CFvon" journalOrPublisher="Tableau encyclopedie et methodique" pageId="205" pageNumber="206" refId="B185" refString="Ledebour, CFvon, 1829. Flora Altaica volume." title="Flora Altaica volume" year="1829">Ledebour 1829</bibRefCitation>
: 225).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C242D950D700490BC7B298BB431393E5" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="BCCEA742B889B8208AF1FAA254D5E661" bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Type.</emphasis>
RUSSIA, Altai, Tiuguriuk stream by Katunja River (LE, not seen).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EB96538215D16D5ACE3394EB8FA2490" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="type">
<paragraph id="A0C5CE2128F0B9490BC8A75F7D59301F" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43A2F4133C78DCD2B720A5BF00F17829" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
KAZAKHSTAN, &quot;in rupestribus montium Tarbagatai ad torrentium Dschanybek&quot;, 
<emphasis id="131542565702C2E8D2BF3F988E518458" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Karelin &amp; Kiriloff</emphasis>
328 (holotype LE ex Herb Ledebour!; isotypes BM001035796!, LE ex herb. Fischer!, LE ex herb. Schrenk!, P!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="450D9305CF96B909EAC0CA840CEE3F73" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="1C9C864B53BE53B5ED6F4F8C41D24F01" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="450240906ADA0BD8D078AD03023602FA" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Distinguished by its suberect habit and triangular leaves, c. 3-5 
<normalizedToken id="CB37EF349316C9D26B9241880D1CD354" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-4 cm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ED4154182D203F3B7EE5B43FACF80DD4" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="48E6E1E1AF2F4DDB0DD301BC3A03424D" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F00ECCE01842F3D5DD5F13C311409BA" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Russia: Siberia (
<emphasis id="7C6C715C895A641B3F68DADFE37C22D6" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Salefov</emphasis>
794, 806 (sin data), 
<emphasis id="D2F9137AE6A399FBE910B94B56BC7E44" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Mardovkin</emphasis>
s.n. (&quot;Siberia altaica&quot;), Kazakhstan (
<emphasis id="CB041B4D912FAF9E0DD274606822BB41" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Karelin &amp; Kiriloff</emphasis>
597 (&quot;Tarbagatai ad torrentium Dschanybek&quot;), 
<emphasis id="918808D7D53C0A462B454F17D3C8DC43" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Roldugin</emphasis>
s.n. [12/8/1960] &quot;Dzungarsky Alatai&quot;), 
<emphasis id="F8D43DE2DDE95547B66E6278F3954879" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Schrenk</emphasis>
s.n. (
<normalizedToken id="1DD42EE8FC56E943C26C71EFDBCA5640" originalValue="“Songaria”">&quot;Songaria&quot;</normalizedToken>
). Apparently rare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="16551CB40A5FD668A701A2D23D27146A" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="notes">
<paragraph id="242C8144E0A27B0380E2A79FBFC0D933" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B176AA158F58A2E363EE51BF25A21709" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="268B9303D9424DFE1664ECBCAA7DF5D9" authorityName="Ker-Gawl., Bot. Reg. 4: t. 322. 1818. (Ker-Gawler" authorityYear="1818" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus chinensis" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="D8897CF015F97757DA6076F2066E3D17" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Convolvulus chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most reliably distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="23A5EF80D655654D39A0EC2947E0176E" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="20AB4C3D183D262CDF04219760F09D9B" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Convolvulus arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the longer sepals. Additionally the auricles are often bifid, the central lobe oblong and the corolla usually deep pink and slightly larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="3332FCDF77BCB5D265A87DDB9C6FEAC9" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="3599C4F6DF6DF225D4A175003DE37AD9" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Convolvulus arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is often considered to be a form of 
<taxonomicName id="15F7803E80B92CD540D031A1C56B50C8" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="7463BD45DE0565BE26919D416BCD9ECF" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Convolvulus arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but intermediates are uncommon, mainly being found in the Tibet region, and could be of hybrid origin. Molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation id="6D4016E16B0BA025CAD14D1283D8F6DC" author="Williams, BRM" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1287 - 1306" publicationUrl="10.12705/636.9" refId="B388" refString="Williams, BRM, Mitchell, TC, Wood, JRI, Harris, DJ, Scotland, RW, Carine, MA, 2014. Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L. Taxon 63: 1287 - 1306, DOI: 10.12705/636.9" title="Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L." url="10.12705/636.9" volume="63" year="2014">Williams et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) strongly support the recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="CE45394D300165778E0AE0A3D7C44592" authorityName="Ker-Gawl., Bot. Reg. 4: t. 322. 1818. (Ker-Gawler" authorityYear="1818" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus chinensis" order="Solanales" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="7EA30EF184B19F40929A72C0E7585101" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Convolvulus chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
